    <h3 id="Status">Status</h3> 

    <p>The following statuses are possible for requests. The (numbers) in front of the text refer to the steps of the request timeline. If you select numbered status it will open the process graph to highlight where that request is in the process. Where no number is shown, this status can occur during multiple steps of the workflow. </p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Waiting for your approval</strong>: the participant requested the course themselves, please approve or reject asap. </li>
        <li><strong>Waiting for processing</strong>: some requests need to be processed by CRO, this should be done within 2 working days at the latest.</li>
        <li><strong>(2) Pending ALC allocation</strong>: we have not yet selected participants for this course. Results of participant selection are typically communicated on 15 May for Semester 2, and 15 November for Semester 1 of the following year. </li>
        <li><strong>(3) Registered</strong>: the participant has a place on the course. You can make travel arrangements.</li>
        <li><strong>(3) Waitlisted</strong>: The candidate does not yet have a place on the course. If a place becomes available, we will email all waitlisted candidates and their focalpoints. The first to confirm will receive the place.</li>
        <li><strong>(4) Confirmed</strong>: the course is now less than 2 months away, and the participant has received the confirmation email. </li>
        <li><strong>(4) Started</strong>: the course is less than 2 months away, or an e-learning course, and the participant has started studying material within the course.</li>
